
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "KrohnDesignsOrdersJava";
}

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row add-top-margin">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-3">
                    <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Projects")" class="">
                        <span class="fa fa-arrow-circle-left"></span> Back to Project Directory
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
                <h2>Krohn Designs Sales Application (Java)</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
                <a href="https://github.com/scottkrohn/KrohnDesignsInventoryMgmt" target="_blank" style="margin-bottom: 10px;" class="btn btn-primary"><span class="fa fa-github-alt"></span> View on Github</a>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
                <p>This is a GUI application to input orders submitted to Krohn Designs written in Java. It's similar in functionality to the other Krohn Designs Sales application I wrote, 
                but rather than storing data a MySql database it stores the data in a serialized java object. You can enter new orders, view past orders, complete orders and edit/delete orders.
                Eventually I am going to add functionality to create supply lists based on the current open orders. 
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12 text-center ">
                    <h4 id="textrpg_description">Main Menu</h4>
                    <img src="~/Content/Images/menu.JPG" id="main_textrpg_image" class="img-responsive center-response-img thin-border"/>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-12 text-center add-top-margin">
                    <a href="" id="thumb" data-large_img="/Content/Images/menu.JPG">
                        <img src="~/Content/Images/Thumbs/menu_thumb.jpg" alt="Main Menu"/></a>
                    <a href="" id="thumb" data-large_img="/Content/Images/neworder.JPG">
                        <img src="~/Content/Images/Thumbs/neworder_thumb.jpg" alt="Submit New Order"/></a>
                    <a href="" id="thumb" data-large_img="/Content/Images/search.JPG">
                        <img src="~/Content/Images/Thumbs/search_thumb.jpg" alt="Search Orders"/></a>
                    <a href="" id="thumb" data-large_img="/Content/Images/vieworders.JPG">
                        <img src="~/Content/Images/Thumbs/vieworders_thumb.jpg" alt="View Orders"/></a>
                    <a href="" id="thumb" data-large_img="/Content/Images/completedorders.JPG">
                        <img src="~/Content/Images/Thumbs/completedorders_thumb.jpg" alt="View Completed Orders"/></a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript" src="~/Scripts/jquery-2.2.3.js"> </script>

<!-- Set the 'src' attribute of the main image based on the thumbnail clicked.-->
<script>
    $("a#thumb").click(function (event) {
        event.preventDefault();
        var fullsize_photo = $(this).data('large_img');
        $("#textrpg_description").html($(this).find("img").attr("alt"));
        $("img#main_textrpg_image").attr("src", fullsize_photo);
    });
</script>



